    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but some people argue that the veto power isn't really a \"flaw\" but actually the only thing that keeps the big powers from just going to war with each other directly. do historians see the UN structure as being fundamentally broken, or is it just a realistic reflection of how power works in the real world?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
