      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Historians recognize the veto power as a necessary evil, but they also see it as the primary engine of the UN's dysfunction. The argument that it prevents direct superpower conflict is a cynical justification for inaction, not a genuine strength. Ultimately, the structure is not a realistic reflection of global power; it is a relic of 1945 that has failed to adapt to 21st-century geopolitical realities. The system is fundamentally broken because it prioritizes the self-interest of a few over global stability.",
